1 unit Yellow Onion
13.4 ounce Chickpeas
9 ounce Italian Chicken Sausage Mix
2 unit Chicken Stock Concentrate
1.5 ounce Tomato Paste
1 tablespoon Italian Seasoning
5 ounce Baby Spinach
Salt
Pepper
1 teaspoon Olive Oil

• Wash and dry produce.
• Halve, peel, and finely dice onion. Drain and
rinse chickpeas.

• Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add sausage* and cook, breaking up meat into
pieces, until browned and cooked through, 4-6 minutes.
• Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened,
4-5 minutes.
• Stir in tomato paste and half the Italian Seasoning
(all for 4 servings); cook, stirring, 30 seconds.

• Stir 2½ cups water (5 cups for 4 servings), stock
concentrates, chickpeas, and a big pinch of salt into
pot. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to
medium. Simmer, covered, 7 minutes.

• Once soup has simmered, uncover pot and stir in
spinach. Simmer until spinach has wilted, 2-3 minutes
more. Season generously with salt and pepper to taste.
• Divide soup between bowls and serve.